  "cooking_instructions": [
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Peel and finely chop the<strong> red onion<span class=\"text-danger\">[s]</span></strong></p>\n<p>Peel and finely chop (or grate) the <strong>garlic</strong></p>\n<p>Heat a large, wide-based pan (preferably non-stick) with a drizzle of <strong>olive oil</strong> over a medium heat</p>\n<p>Once hot, add the <strong>chopped onion</strong>, <strong>chopped garlic</strong> and <strong>dried chilli flakes</strong> (can't handle the heat? Go easy!) and cook for 3-4 min or until softened</p>",
      "order": 1,
      "image": "/images/instructions/smoked-mackerel-arrabbiata-linguine/step-1.jpg"
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Meanwhile, boil a kettle</p>\n<p>Add the<strong> linguine</strong> to a pot of <strong>boiled water</strong> with a large pinch of <strong>salt</strong> and bring to the boil over a high heat</p>\n<p>Cook the <strong>linguine</strong> for 8-10 min or until cooked with a slight bite</p>\n<p>Once done, drain the <strong>linguine</strong>, reserving a cup of the <strong>starchy pasta water</strong></p>",
      "order": 2,
      "image": "/images/instructions/smoked-mackerel-arrabbiata-linguine/step-2.jpg"
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Whilst the linguine is cooking, add the <strong>chopped tomatoes</strong> and <strong>tomato paste</strong> to the pan with the <strong>softened onion</strong> and stir it all together</p>\n<p>Season with a grind of<strong> black</strong> <strong>pepper</strong> and bring to the boil over a high heat</p>",
      "order": 3,
      "image": "/images/instructions/smoked-mackerel-arrabbiata-linguine/step-3.jpg"
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Remove the skin from the<strong> smoked mackerel fillets</strong></p>\n<p>Tip: Watch out for any tiny bones and discard them</p>\n<p>Tear the <strong>smoked mackerel</strong> into rough pieces </p>\n<p>Slice the<strong> black olives</strong> finely</p>",
      "order": 4,
      "image": "/images/instructions/smoked-mackerel-arrabbiata-linguine/step-4.jpg"
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Crumble 1/2 <span class=\"text-danger\">[1]</span> <strong>Knorr vegetable stock cube </strong>into the pan and add a couple of splashes of <strong>starchy pasta water</strong> </p>\n<p>Give everything a stir, reduce the heat to medium and cook for 5-6 min or until a thick pasta sauce remains</p>",
      "order": 5,
      "image": "/images/instructions/smoked-mackerel-arrabbiata-linguine/step-5.jpg"
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Once thickened, add the<strong> sliced black olives</strong> and<strong> torn mackerel</strong> to the pan and stir it all together – this is your <strong>smoked mackerel arrabbiata sauce</strong></p>",
      "order": 6,
      "image": "/images/instructions/smoked-mackerel-arrabbiata-linguine/step-6.jpg"
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Chop the<strong> basil</strong> finely, including the stalks</p>\n<p>Add the <strong>drained linguine</strong> and <strong>chopped basil</strong> to the <strong>smoked mackerel arrabbiata sauce</strong> and give everything a good mix up</p>\n<p>Tip: Add a splash more starchy pasta water if your sauce is looking a little dry</p>",
      "order": 7,
      "image": "/images/instructions/smoked-mackerel-arrabbiata-linguine/step-7.jpg"
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Serve the <strong>smoked mackerel arrabbiata linguine</strong> topped with a handful of <strong>rocket</strong></p>\n<p>Drizzle with some <strong>olive oil</strong> and season with a good grind of <strong>black pepper</strong></p>\n<p>Enjoy!</p>",
      "order": 8
    }
  ],
